217
00:08:49,062 --> 00:08:50,130
Let's move on.

218
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:51,498
In Korea,

219
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:55,535
people don't normally make dumplings
at home, right?

220
00:08:55,602 --> 00:08:57,670
-Yes, we do.
-You do?

221
00:08:57,737 --> 00:08:58,805
On Lunar New Year.

222
00:08:58,872 --> 00:09:00,140
-Really?
-Yes.

223
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,409
And we make dumpling soup

224
00:09:02,475 --> 00:09:04,477
called mandu-guk.

225
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,779
Do you eat the soup too?

226
00:09:05,845 --> 00:09:08,048
-Yes, we do.
-Really?

227
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,250
Soup plays a big part in Korean cuisine.

228
00:09:10,784 --> 00:09:12,252
Gukbap, soup with rice.

229
00:09:12,318 --> 00:09:13,953
Naeng-myun, noodles in cold soup.

230
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:17,924
So Koreans often gain weight
when they first come to Japan.

231
00:09:17,991 --> 00:09:20,060
They'd get rich pork-bone ramen

232
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:21,895
and finish all the broth.

233
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:24,297
-In Japan, that's…
-I know.

234
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:27,033
We feel guilty.

235
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,401
-Some drink it,
-I see.

236
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:29,669
but those around them

237
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:32,739
give them cold stares,
thinking "Did they just drink the broth?"

238
00:09:32,872 --> 00:09:35,675
Have you had naeng-myun?

239
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:39,979
Well, speaking frankly,

240
00:09:40,213 --> 00:09:42,916
I've never had naeng-myun
that made me say "Wow."

241
00:09:42,982 --> 00:09:44,584
Please leave it to me.

242
00:09:44,784 --> 00:09:47,353
There's a place
all my Japanese friends loved.

243
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,422
They say
"So this is what real naeng-myun is!"

244
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:51,925
-Really?
-And that they might get addicted to it.

245
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:55,428
Does that mean it's hard to find
a good naeng-myun place in Japan?

246
00:09:56,062 --> 00:09:57,464
Honestly, yes.

247
00:09:57,564 --> 00:09:59,265
-Is that so?
-Even in Korea.

248
00:09:59,332 --> 00:10:01,267
That's crucial information.

249
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:03,937
-Well, it isn’t easy.
-I see.

250
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:06,873
They add too much seasoning.
It happens in Korea too, but…

251
00:10:07,574 --> 00:10:08,708
