291
00:12:08,127 --> 00:12:09,128
SICHUAN, THE HOMELAND OF SPICE

292
00:12:09,195 --> 00:12:10,063
-Sichuan?
-Yes.

293
00:12:10,129 --> 00:12:12,865
-Sichuan has a lot of spicy dishes, right?
-That's right.

294
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:17,070
There are a lot of mountains in Sichuan,
so work can be tough there.

295
00:12:17,136 --> 00:12:18,605
Usually, roads aren't flat.

296
00:12:18,671 --> 00:12:23,142
You need to carry loads
and climb up the mountains.

297
00:12:23,209 --> 00:12:25,511
Tan means to carry.

298
00:12:25,712 --> 00:12:27,280
That's why it’s called tantanmen.

299
00:12:27,347 --> 00:12:29,349
-Tan means shouldering?
-That's right.

300
00:12:29,549 --> 00:12:31,251
-That's what it meant.
-Yes.

301
00:12:31,551 --> 00:12:35,922
TANTANMEN: NOODLES CARRIED ON A POLE

